values: Arrrrrg! I am so frustrated with some of my classmates right now! I just got done working with a group on a presentation we have to do next Monday and it was not pretty (I'm sure the rest of the group thought it was fine but that's only because they couldn't actually hear anything that I was trying to say). This group seems to have decided what they want all of the answers to be and then done research to prove what they wanted to be correct. Perhaps this is just the scientist in me lashing out but that isn't research (it's politics)! There was a serious problem with knowing the difference between fact and opinion and that lead to some pretty serious oversights also. Overall, it was a pretty horrendous group meeting and seems like it is going to be a presentation where i just spout off the information I have found on the internet and don't bother explaining or going into detail or the presentation will turn into a debate (and probably not a pretty one). I think that what really puts me over the edge in so many of these discussions here is that we look at scientific topics but leave the science out of the picture. We look at biological issues and solve them based strictly on feelings or we look at geological issues and try to apply emotional solutions to them and sometimes things just don't work that way. Usually ranting helps me to vent but I'm actually getting more fired up (and my words aren't working for me) now so I'm going to stop. There may or may not be more of this rant yet to come. Have a great day!

Ugh! Monday... Monday is my super long day and I want to be outside. It is supposed to rain today which would make being inside all day a bit easier but I really want to go fly a kite and play frisbee and then end the day with a good game of softball! That sounds like a great day! Guess I'll be dreaming about that as I sit through 9 hours of class, a potluck and a meeting over the course of the next 13 hours. At least I like all of my classes. I have a little paper due this evening that I haven't started yet so I'm going t be working on that during class today. Well, happy Monday, readers!

So this morning church made me really scared for what is going to happen at my church when I am gone. On Easter, between the sunrise service and the regular service, we always have a breakfast. All week I have been trying to figure out who was in charge of it so that I knew if people were supposed to bring stuff or not. Turns out the reason that I couldn't find whoever was supposed to be in charge was because NO ONE was in charge of it. No one made the coffee or organized the event. Not a huge deal but still ridiculous. Then, we had an egg hunt scheduled for 9:00 and when no one was there yet at 8:30 to hide the nearly 300 eggs that I made the youth prepare Friday night I hid them (I was not in charge of this either). I don't mind doing these things but soon I am not going to be there anymore and then they are not going to be able to just plan things and not plan on having people there to carry them out. I feel really bad and am really scared for my church but I cannot help them with this one (because I am not going to be there which is why this is an issue). 

My sister-in-laws parents are in town right now and they are awesome! I love when they are in town. We went to the Spaghetti Factory last night for her birthday and it was a great time! Now I am working on lunch for the whole family and that is going to be a good time to! So far its been a good day but it has already made me aware of the issues that are going to come from the next several years at least.

Well, this is holy week and holy week for a seminary student is crazy even if you don't have a church placement (who'd have guessed that, right?). I was talked into chaperoning a lock-in Friday night after the Good Friday service and I think it is going to be great but I also think that Good Friday needs to bring to light some of the suffering of Christianity and so I want to do a Bible study that will make the kids cry but feel like that's probably not a good idea.... Idk... Hopefully the Good Friday service will make me cry and then I can get that out of my system. 

In other news, my grandma has been having some problems with her blood pressure lately and when she went to the hospital last week they told her that if it keeps happening, she is going to have to be put on a monitor for a while and that may lead to a pace maker. So now she is going around telling people that she is getting a pacemaker... NOT WHAT THE DOCTOR SAID GRANDMA!!! So now people are calling me and e-mail me to express their concern about Grandma getting a pacemaker and it just isn't true. My grandma needs a hobby because otherwise she picks something to fixate on and drives everyone crazy. Sometimes its a good thing (usually its a bad thing) but always she gets the story wrong, exaggerates, and makes people go crazy. 

I'm looking forward to this crazy, sleep-free weekend. Tomorrow seining, then fish fry, church, lock-in. Then, Saturday  Cardinals training (for fund raising), games with some friends from home, and then hanging out. Sunday, EASTER!!!!

There's probably more I should write about but that's all I can think of for now and I'm out of time. More ranting to come :)

Hello again, 
    It has now been almost 3 years since my last post. I cannot believe how high school I was in my previous posts. Since my last post I have graduation from college and am now attending Seminary. I now rarely say the word angst and even more rarely type it. I currently spend 10 hours a week at Nurses for Newborns (which is where I am now) and am supposed to do work on grants and things while I'm there (which I'm obviously not doing). Turns out that once you get senioritis it never goes away. In fact it seems to get worse and worse as I go through more and more school (and I'm not even a senior anymore). I don't really know much else today but intend to start posting things here much more frequently. I tried journaling last fall and I did great for about 2 months and haven't picked it up since so maybe if I try to update here several times a week it will serve the same purpose. Have a great day!
Sometimes I come to this page and I type up a long angsty post and then I delete it.

I went trick-or-treating this evening and it was WONDERFUL!!! There were a bunch of people from my floor who went and we got candy and collected canned goods. We went to the rich part of town (which, untill this evening i didn't know existed). I got to go into one of the richy-rich houses and it was awesome. They had the most amazing kitched I had ever seen!!! I have a whole weeks worth of Physics homework to do right now but I'm just too excited to do it. Oh, in case you were wondering I was dressed up as Little Red Riding Hood and I was told it was pretty adorable (although I think that I looked like Rufus, blech!). Oh and HOUSE IS BACK!!!! I LOVE TODAY!!! (post 10:00AM today) WOOT!!!!!!!!!!

So yesterday I got my slave to clean my room. It's pretty awesome! Here are some pictures Before: After: He clead everything; from vacuuming to washing my roommate out of her bed! Amazing, isn't it? On a completely different note, Saturday I'm going to the Melting Pot and it's gonna be SUPER awesome!!! All is well with the world.

Well, my roommate finially decided to break up with her boyfriend. So, tomorrow I'm driving her to Spingfield, MO and back so that neither of them have to drive after their break-up conversation. Any ideas for things to do to occupy myself for an hour or so in Springfield? This could be very interesting.... I love college!

Dear journal, 
       He's STILL here. The boy in my roommate's bed just never leaves. I'm really tired of all the snuggling and grossness that goes on (especially since she has a boyfriend and it's NOT the boy in her bed)! I got a shot this afternoon. It was the best part of my day!!! In other news, I got a 95% on my physics test the other day. That was pretty exicitng. I actually made my self write my lab report last night (which is good cause it was due today). It took me four and a half hours and is 11 pages long. Now I have to go to my "Yea! You're a girl class". WOOHOO!!!

I have one question for the world.... WTF WORLD!?! So, my room is really weird right now. Greg and Emily came and visted me Monday/Tuesday (and Emily, Sunday) and I LOVE them!!!! Now, I'm left to face this room all by my self and I'm supposed to be writing my lab report but I think it's pretty obvious that i'm not doing that. Mikey is coming home this weekend and i can't wait. My roommate is also coming home with me this weekend. I was excited about that but now i'm not so sure.... I think it will be fun. I'm not really sure what to think about anything right now. I give up!

I'm updating.... this seems SO weird. I don't quite know what to say but all the cool kids were updating so I thought i should too. Life has been going pretty good. UMR is awesome but this week kinda sucks! It's the week before Midterms so for some reason I have a bunch of midterms this week. The teachers are all like "we want to spread your tests out for you so we are going to have our midterm a week early." The problem is that ALL of the teachers did that so i have a buttload of tests this week. oh well! Well, that's enough posting for me. This is weird!

OMG i'm going to new york and i may be seeing rent on broadway!!! AND i don't have to go to my church's good friday service because i will be in new york. 

yesterday i got my wisdom teeth removed and it was awesome. Now i have all kinds of good meds and i don't have to go to school. i don't even feel bad, i'm just at home doing whatever i feel like doing. This whole staying at home thing is the best! 

I've also decided that i'm going to prom and i'm pretty sure that all of my friends have gotten over it and aren't mad at me anymore. I've got my dress and all my other stuff and i don't need to worry about it any more. 

Thursday i will go back to school and then friday i'm going to a math competition so i will only have one day of school this week! This week is GREAT!!!
What should be my main criteria for choosing my college? I hate major decisions!!!
GO STEELERS!!!!! Hmmm, my eye itches but when I rub it it hurts. I wonder why!
I have super senioritis! Oh yeah, and ANGST ANGST ANGST!!!

Cab you believe that none of these old people are up at quarter after 2 in the morning :S I don't know what i'm going to do for the next four hours I watched the movie Without A Paddle while "doing laundry" and it was funny and took up about 2 hours so that was good. Now i'm out of things that i was supposed to get done over night and am finding it hard to stay awake. It wouldn't be bad if there was anything that needed to be done here but there isn't so i'm really bored and that makes me sleepy! Well it's time for me to go search for stuff to do to keep me awake. (you know that i'm bored if i'm taking the time to update my journal!)
